		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27440933">So I <!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/reviews.php?id=126873">wrote a kawaii review</a> for Kyousou Giga, which I think deservedly won this award. Being top-notched in terms of cast, main character, animation, and many more, this title is best given to Kyousou Giga. And as a whole, Kyousou Giga is just a cohesive series that amalgamates its versatile traits properly, earning it perhaps not only the title of AOTY, but also one of the best anime in recent years. <br />
<br />
Runner-up contestants:<br />
<ul><br />
<li>Uchouten Kazoku (which I think I'd like a lot, but unfortunately I haven't gotten the time to look into yet)<br />
<li>Monogatari Season II (quality show; still trying to finish it)<br />
<li>Turning Girls (because reasons) <br />
</ul></ol></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
