		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27442377">Mine would have to be Chihayafuru 2. I didn't even feel that it aired this year because I did a marathon on it when it finished. But nevertheless, I really love the series and I felt season 2 was a great addition, even if it lacked romance or interactions with moreso karuta games. It was thoroughly entertaining, memorable and had lots of moments where it just striked a chord in my heart and made me in tears. Madhouse's execution is just lovable and I loved the directing. Even if it is predictable at times and somewhat slow, the show didn't rely on predictability or shock factor on its story, and I like slow pacing more than fast pacing so lucky for me. (I even wrote a <!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/anime/14397/Chihayafuru_2/reviews">review</a> on it so if that saids anything about my love...)<br />
<br />
I guess I'll do runner up contestants like Stellio too:<br />
 - Kyousougiga (pretty much what Stellio said)<br />
 - Kill la Kill (I know it's a bit controversial but honestly, I enjoyed it immensely and it had a slight nostalgic atmosphere, plus great animation style (read: not budget) and OST with memorable characters that voice acts too well and I can care for. An action series I find inspiring to myself. I just hope the 2nd half takes the cliches the last episodes put forward and does something amazing)<br />
 - Uchouten Kazoku (was hard to follow at first, but kicks in after episode 3 and is very clever in its writing and was generally creative and thought-provoking. Episode 8 ;__;)<br />
 - GJ-bu (really liked it, was a rather relaxing, chill series that didn't try too hard to keep the viewers in, but does it with delicacy and warmth. A slow slice of life series that I personally love because of its fun characters and chill atmosphere; ending was really sweet too)</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=35120"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/6PN7YGc.png" /></a><br />
Me blog: <a href="http://tobunation.wordpress.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://tobunation.wordpress.com/</a></div></td>
