		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27450431">I'll also go with Kyousougiga, and agree wholeheartedly with Stellio's post and review. The visuals and sound were fantastic and the writing was of a consistently high quality, enhanced by some clever uses of foreshadowing and symbolism.<br />
<br />
Runner-ups:<br />
<ul><br />
<li>Monogatari Series Second Season (enhanced its prequels a lot, especially in terms of character depth)<br />
<li>Uchouten Kazoku (very well-written with unique and likable characters)<br />
<li>Hidamari Sketch: Sae Hiro Sotsugyou-hen (a great possible conclusion to the franchise's anime adaptation)<br />
</ul></ol></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
