		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27899739">I'll be a bummer and go with Kyousougiga followed by Uchouten Kazoku. <br />
<br />
I would like to give special mention to the Teekyu seasons that aired this year. It follows the path paved by the first season, but improves upon it rather than making it feel dragged out (which comedy shorts often tend to do after a while). Its no more than but also no less than 2 minutes of pure, condensed and intense fun which oozes creativity and bizarrity. Keeping up with this show is more difficult than trying to interpret Mind Game or the last few minutes of Evangelion. Teekyu is an experience like no other.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
